external_knowledge:
- "lightning-fast" refers to the racers with the highest average speed on their respective tracks;
- "first to cross the finish line" implies they have the highest speed rank (ranked 1) for their track;
- "outshine the average performance" means their speed is greater than the average speed of all racers.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the top-performing racers;
- 'Measure up' refers to their average lap time and speed metrics;
- 'Top 3 racers' are those with the fastest average lap times within their respective teams.

- `race_id` is a unique identifier for each race;
- `lap_speed` represents the speed achieved during a lap in the race;
- `race_name` is the name of the race event.

sql:
SELECT r.racer_name
FROM racers r
JOIN performance_metrics pm ON r.racer_id = pm.racer_id;

SELECT MIN(lap_time) AS fastest_lap_time
FROM laps
WHERE race_id = 1;

SELECT race_id, COUNT(lap_id) AS total_laps
FROM laps
GROUP BY race_id;

external_knowledge:
- Fast racers are defined as those who have an average speed greater than 200 and have completed at least 50 laps in a race;
- Officials are users with a role of '0';
- The query focuses on events and access logs that occurred on the same day.

- "average speed" is a measure of how fast racers complete the race on average;
- "overall average speed" refers to the average speed of all racers across all races;
- "races" are events where racers compete, and each race has a unique identifier and name.
